d industrial growth, population increase, deforestation, and the overconsumption of natural resources all play significant roles. Many industries release untreated waste into the environment, while individuals often lack awareness about proper waste management. The widespread use of single-use plastics has also worsened the problem.\\n\\nThe effects of environmental pollution are far-reaching and severe. It leads to various health problems, including asthma, heart disease, and even cancer. Furthermore, pollution contributes to climate change, which causes rising temperatures, extreme weather events, and the loss of biodiversity. Ecosystems are disrupted, and many species face extinction as their natural habitats are destroyed.\\n\\nTo address this issue, both individuals and governments must take responsibility. Individuals can reduce waste, recycle materials, and adopt eco-friendly habits such as using public transportation and minimizing plastic use. Governments should implement strict environmental regulations, promote renewable energy sources, and invest in sustainable development. Education and awareness campaigns are also essential to encourage people to protect the environment.\\n\\nIn conclusion, environmental pollution is a global problem that requires urgent and collective action. By changing our behaviors and enforcing effective policies, we can reduce pollution and preserve the planet for future generations.\"',_binary '',29,137,'Bài viết đã đạt được yêu cầu đề bài, trình bày rõ ràng và mạch lạc. Tuy nhiên, vẫn cần cải thiện về vốn từ vựng và độ chính xác ngữ pháp.','{\"task_achievement\":9,\"lexical_resource\":8,\"grammar\":9,\"coherence_cohesion\":10}',36,_binary '\0',NULL),(86,'\"Environmental pollution is one of the most serious challenges facing the modern world. As industrialization and urbanization continue to expand, the natural environment is increasingly exposed to harmful substances and destructive human activities. Pollution not only damages ecosystems but also threatens human health and the sustainability of life on Earth.\\n\\nThere are several major types of environmental pollution, including air, water, soil, and noise pollution. Air pollution is primarily caused by emissions from vehicles, factories, and the burning of fossil fuels, leading to serious health issues such as respiratory diseases and contributing to global warming. Water pollution occurs when industrial waste, chemicals, and plastic debris are discharged into rivers, lakes, and oceans, endangering aquatic life and contaminating drinking water sources. Soil pollution results from the excessive use of pesticides, fertilizers, and improper waste disposal, which reduce land fertility and affect food production. Additionally, noise pollution from traffic and construction disrupts both human life and wildlife.\\n\\nThe causes of pollution are largely linked to human activities. Rapid industrial growth, population increase, deforestation, and the overconsumption of natural resources all play significant roles. Many industries release untreated waste into the environment, while individuals often lack awareness about proper waste management. The widespread use of single-use plastics has also worsened the problem.\\n\\nThe effects of environmental pollution are far-reaching and severe. It leads to various health problems, including asthma, heart disease, and even cancer. Furthermore, pollution contributes to climate change, which causes rising temperatures, extreme weather events, and the loss of biodiversity. Ecosystems are disrupted, and many species face extinction as their natural habitats are destroyed.\\n\\nTo address this issue, both individuals and governments must take responsibility. Individuals can reduce waste, recycle materials, and adopt eco-friendly habits such as using public transportation and minimizing plastic use. Governments should implement strict environmental regulations, promote renewable energy sources, and invest in sustainable development. Education and awareness campaigns are also essential to encourage people to protect the environment.\\n\\nIn conclusion, environmental pollution is a global problem that requires urgent and collective action. By changing our behaviors and enforcing effective policies, we can reduce pollution and preserve the planet for future generations.\"',_binary '',30,137,'Bài viết đã hoàn thành tốt yêu cầu đề bài, trình bày rõ ràng và mạch lạc. Tuy nhiên, vẫn cần cải thiện vốn từ vựng và độ chính xác ngữ pháp để đạt điểm cao hơn.','{\"task_achievement\":9,\"lexical_resource\":8,\"grammar\":9,\"coherence_cohesion\":10}',36,_binary '\0',NULL),(87,'\"Environment pollution is one of the most serious global challenges facing humanity today. It occurs when harmful substances—such as chemicals, waste, or noise—are introduced into the natural environment, causing damage to ecosystems and human health. Pollution affects the air we breathe, the water we drink, and the land we depend on for food and shelter.\\n\\nAir pollution is perhaps the most visible and dangerous type. It is mainly caused by emissions from vehicles, factories, and the burning of fossil fuels. In many large cities, thick layers of smog cover the skyline, making it difficult for people to breathe and increasing the risk of respiratory diseases such as asthma and lung cancer. Long-term exposure to polluted air can significantly reduce life expectancy.\\n\\nWater pollution is another critical issue. Rivers, lakes, and oceans are often contaminated by industrial waste, agricultural chemicals, and plastic debris. Marine life suffers greatly as fish and other organisms ingest toxic substances or become trapped in plastic waste. Additionally, polluted water sources can lead to serious health problems for humans, including infections and poisoning.\\n\\nLand pollution, caused by improper waste disposal and excessive use of chemicals, also has severe consequences. Landfills are growing rapidly, and non-biodegradable materials such as plastic can take hundreds of years to decompose. Deforestation, often driven by human activities like agriculture and urban development, further worsens the situation by destroying natural habitats and contributing to climate change.\\n\\nThe effects of environmental pollution are far-reaching. It not only harms wildlife and natural ecosystems but also threatens human survival. Climate change, which is closely linked to pollution, leads to rising sea levels, extreme weather events, and disruptions in food production.\\n\\nTo address this issue, individuals and governments must work together. Reducing the use of plastic, recycling waste, conserving energy, and promoting renewable energy sources are essential steps. Governments should also enforce stricter environmental regulations and invest in sustainable development.\\n\\nIn conclusion, environmental pollution is a pressing issue that requires immediate attention. Protecting the environment is not just a responsibility but a necessity to ensure a healthy and sustainable future for generations to come.\"',_binary '',31,137,'Bài viết của bạn đã đề cập đến các vấn đề chính về ô nhiễm môi trường, nhưng có thể cải thiện về vốn từ vựng và cấu trúc câu. Hãy tiếp tục phát triển kỹ năng viết của mình!','{\"task_achievement\":8,\"lexical_resource\":6,\"grammar\":7,\"coherence_cohesion\":7}',28,_binary '\0',NULL),(88,'\"https://res.cloudinary.com/decqv3ed0/video/upload/v1775498012/vfsqaxgohzjpznptuqoe.webm\"',_binary '\0',32,136,'Học sinh không trả lời câu hỏi về gia đình, thay vào đó là một câu mời đăng ký kênh. Cần tập trung vào chủ đề và trả lời câu hỏi một cách rõ ràng và liên quan.','{\"fluency_cohesion\":{\"score\":0.0,\"max\":9.0,\"bandLabel\":\"0\",\"bandDescription\":\"Cannot communicate\",\"aiReasoning\":\"Học sinh không thể diễn đạt ý tưởng của mình một cách rõ ràng và liên tục.\"},\"lexical_resource\":{\"score\":0.0,\"max\":9.0,\"bandLabel\":\"0\",\"bandDescription\":\"No appropriate lexical resource\",\"aiReasoning\":\"Học sinh không sử dụng từ vựng phù hợp với chủ đề.\"},\"grammatical_range\":{\"score\":0.0,\"max\":9.0,\"bandLabel\":\"0\",\"bandDescription\":\"No grammatical structures\",\"aiReasoning\":\"Học sinh không sử dụng cấu trúc ngữ pháp nào.\"},\"pronunciation\":{\"score\":0.0,\"max\":9.0,\"bandLabel\":\"0\",\"bandDescription\":\"No intelligible pronunciation\",\"aiReasoning\":\"Học sinh không thể phát âm một cách rõ ràng và dễ hiểu.\"}}',0,_binary '\0',NULL),(89,'\"Environmental pollution is one of the most serious challenges facing the modern world. It refers to the contamination of natural resources such as air, water, and soil by harmful substances, often as a result of human activities. As industrialization and urbanization continue to grow, pollution has become a global issue that affects ecosystems, human health, and the overall balance of the planet.\\n\\nAir pollution is caused mainly by emissions from factories, vehicles, and the burning of fossil fuels. Harmful gases such as carbon dioxide, sulfur dioxide, and nitrogen oxides contribute to problems like climate change, acid rain, and respiratory diseases. In many large cities, poor air quality has become a daily concern, reducing the quality of life and increasing health risks.\\n\\nWater pollution occurs when waste materials, chemicals, and plastics are discharged into rivers, lakes, and oceans. This not only harms aquatic life but also affects people who rely on these water sources for drinking, agriculture, and daily use. Oil spills, industrial waste, and untreated sewage are some of the main causes of water contamination.\\n\\nSoil pollution is another major issue, often resulting from the excessive use of pesticides, fertilizers, and improper disposal of industrial and household waste. Contaminated soil can lead to reduced agricultural productivity and the spread of toxic substances into the food chain, ultimately affecting human health.\\n\\nThe consequences of environmental pollution are far-reaching. It leads to the loss of biodiversity, climate change, and serious health problems such as asthma, cancer, and cardiovascular diseases. Moreover, pollution threatens the sustainability of future generations by depleting natural resources and damaging ecosystems.\\n\\nTo address environmental pollution, both governments and individuals must take action. Governments should enforce stricter environmental regulations, promote renewable energy, and invest in sustainable technologies. Individuals can contribute by reducing waste, recycling, conserving energy, and using environmentally friendly products.\\n\\nIn conclusion, environmental pollution is a critical issue that requires immediate and collective efforts. Protecting the environment is not only essential for our well-being but also for the survival of all living organisms on Earth.\"',_binary '',33,137,'Bài viết đã trình bày rõ ràng và đầy đủ về vấn đề ô nhiễm môi trường, đưa ra các ví dụ và giải pháp cụ thể. Tuy nhiên, để cải thiện, cần tăng cường sử dụng từ vựng đa dạng và phức tạp hơn, cũng như phát triển các ý tưởng một cách sâu sắc hơn.','{\"task_achievement\":{\"score\":8.0,\"max\":9.0,\"bandLabel\":\"Band 8.0\",\"bandDescription\":\"Satisfies all requirements; very good development and cohesion\",\"aiReasoning\":\"Bài viết đã đáp ứng đầy đủ yêu cầu của đề bài, trình bày rõ ràng và logic về vấn đề ô nhiễm môi trường, đưa ra các ví dụ và giải pháp cụ thể.\"},\"lexical_resource\":{\"score\":8.0,\"max\":9.0,\"bandLabel\":\"Band 8.0\",\"bandDescription\":\"Wide range; very few lexical errors; communicates flexibly\",\"aiReasoning\":\"Bài viết đã sử dụng từ vựng đa dạng và phù hợp, tuy nhiên vẫn có thể cải thiện bằng cách sử dụng từ vựng phức tạp hơn và tránh lặp lại từ ngữ.\"},\"grammatical_range\":{\"score\":8.0,\"max\":9.0,\"bandLabel\":\"Band 8.0\",\"bandDescription\":\"Wide range; very good accuracy; rare errors\",\"aiReasoning\":\"Bài viết đã thể hiện sự đa dạng về cấu trúc ngữ pháp, sử dụng cả câu đơn và câu phức, tuy nhiên vẫn có thể cải thiện bằng cách sử dụng cấu trúc ngữ pháp phức tạp hơn.\"},\"coherence_cohesion\":{\"score\":8.5,\"max\":9.0,\"bandLabel\":\"Band 8.5\",\"bandDescription\":\"Very well organized; seamless cohesion\",\"aiReasoning\":\"Bài viết đã được tổ chức rõ ràng và logic, sử dụng các từ nối và cụm từ chuyển tiếp để kết nối các ý tưởng một cách mượt mà.\"}}',21,_binary '\0',NULL);
