ts have already taken the quiz, and their results have been recorded. The quiz is being administered by a team of teachers who have been trained to use the new software. The software, which has been developed by a leading company, is being used in many schools because it is easy to use and very efficient. The company has also provided training for the teachers, which has been very helpful.',NULL,'READING','DRAFT','Quiz từ vựng mới',11,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2026-04-18 06:03:15.892687'),(42,NULL,'5.0','2026-04-18 06:03:15.897223',NULL,'The new vocabulary quiz has been designed by experts who have been working on it for several months. The quiz, which has been made available online, is intended for students who have been preparing for the exam and want to test their knowledge. Many students have already taken the quiz, and their results have been recorded. The quiz is being administered by a team of teachers who have been trained to use the new software. The software, which has been developed by a leading company, is being used in many schools because it is easy to use and very efficient. The company has also provided training for the teachers, which has been very helpful.',NULL,'READING','DRAFT','Quiz từ vựng mới',11,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2026-04-18 06:03:15.897223'),(43,NULL,'5.0','2026-04-18 06:03:15.901247',NULL,'The new vocabulary quiz has been designed by experts who have been working on it for several months. The quiz, which has been made available online, is intended for students who have been preparing for the exam and want to test their knowledge. Many students have already taken the quiz, and their results have been recorded. The quiz is being administered by a team of teachers who have been trained to use the new software. The software, which has been developed by a leading company, is being used in many schools because it is easy to use and very efficient. The company has also provided training for the teachers, which has been very helpful.',NULL,'READING','DRAFT','Quiz từ vựng mới',11,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2026-04-18 06:03:15.901247'),(44,NULL,'3.0','2026-04-19 10:39:57.334514',NULL,'Mark [Male]: Hi Sarah. Are you ready for the quiz?\nSarah [Female]: Hi Mark. Yes, I am. I think it starts now.\nMark [Male]: Oh, really? I thought it began at two o\'clock.\nSarah [Female]: No, it was twenty-thirty, wasn\'t it? The email said so.\nMark [Male]: You are right. I checked my phone. It\'s twenty-thirty.\nSarah [Female]: Okay. What is the topic today?\nMark [Male]: It is \"General Knowledge,\" first session. We need to answer ten questions.\nSarah [Female]: Ten questions? That sounds like a lot for one quiz.\nMark [Male]: Yes, but they are easy, I hope. We have twenty minutes for them.\nSarah [Female]: Twenty minutes. That is good. Did you study anything?\nMark [Male]: A little. I read some facts about history.\nSarah [Female]: Oh, history. I like history! Let\'s start.',NULL,'LISTENING','DRAFT','Quiz — Buổi 1',11,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2026-04-19 10:39:57.334514'),(45,NULL,'3.0','2026-04-19 11:07:22.522231',NULL,'Sarah [Female]: Hello, Tom. Are you ready for our quiz today?\nTom [Male]: Hi, Sarah. Yes, I am. I studied for it yesterday.\nSarah [Female]: Great! This is Quiz - Session 1. It has five questions.\nTom [Male]: Five questions. Okay. What is the first question about?\nSarah [Female]: The first question is about animals. Listen carefully.\nTom [Male]: Animals. My favorite!\nSarah [Female]: Question one: Which animal can fly and lays eggs?\nTom [Male]: Hmm. An animal that flies and lays eggs. Is it a bird?\nSarah [Female]: Yes, Tom, that is correct! A bird. Good job.\nTom [Male]: Yay! I got one right.\nSarah [Female]: Now, question two. This is about history. When did the first man walk on the moon?\nTom [Male]: Oh, history is hard. I think it was in 1969. Neil Armstrong.\nSarah [Female]: That\'s also correct! You are doing very well today, Tom.\nTom [Male]: Thank you, Sarah. I like this quiz.\nSarah [Female]: Me too. We can do more next week.',NULL,'LISTENING','DRAFT','Quiz — Buổi 1',11,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2026-04-19 11:07:22.522231'),(46,NULL,'4.0','2026-04-19 11:39:24.877570',NULL,'David [Male]: Hi Sarah, how was Quiz Buổi 2 for you yesterday?\nSarah [Female]: Oh, hi David! It was fun, but quite challenging. I think I did okay.\nDavid [Male]: Really? I found the history questions very difficult. Especially the one about ancient kings.\nSarah [Female]: Yes, that one was tricky! I guessed the answer. What about the science round? Did you like it?\nDavid [Male]: The science round was better for me. I knew the answer about the planets. That was easy.\nSarah [Female]: Good for you! I always struggle with science. I prefer the literature part.\nDavid [Male]: Ah, I see. My favorite part was the music round. They played some good songs.\nSarah [Female]: Oh, I missed that! I was still thinking about the history questions. Did you get a good score?\nDavid [Male]: Not bad. I got 7 out of 10. How about you?\nSarah [Female]: I got 6. So you did better than me! We should study for the next one.\nDavid [Male]: Definitely! Buổi 3 is next week. We can meet before it.\nSarah [Female]: That\'s a great idea! I will bring my notes.\nDavid [Male]: Perfect. See you then!',NULL,'LISTENING','PUBLISHED','Quiz — Buổi 2',11,'','2026-04-19 12:08:17.175666',3,'2026-04-19 12:08:17.176698'),(47,NULL,'4.5','2026-04-20 04:21:27.820197',NULL,'Sarah [Female]: Hi David. Did you try the new listening quiz online? Miss Green put it up yesterday.\nDavid [Male]: Oh, hi Sarah. Yes, I did! I finished it this morning. It was quite interesting.\nSarah [Female]: Really? I haven\'t started it yet. What was it about?\nDavid [Male]: It was about a family planning their summer holiday. They talked about different places they could go.\nSarah [Female]: Hmm, sounds useful. Were the questions difficult?\nDavid [Male]: Some were. For example, there was a question about *when* they wanted to go. The answer was in July, but they mentioned June first, then changed their mind. You really had to listen carefully.\nSarah [Female]: Ah, I see. What about the people? Were they easy to understand?\nDavid [Male]: Yes, they spoke clearly. The man had a slightly deeper voice than the woman. And their children also spoke a little.\nSarah [Female]: Okay, good to know. I usually find it hard when people speak too fast.\nDavid [Male]: This one was a good speed. There was also a question about the budget. They talked about how much money they wanted to spend.\nSarah [Female]: And what was their budget? Do you remember?\nDavid [Male]: Yes, I think they said they wanted to spend around 2000 pounds for the whole trip. They thought it was a good amount.\nSarah [Female]: Wow, that\'s a lot! I hope I can remember all these details when I do it.\nDavid [Male]: You will be fine. Just focus on the key information. I found it helpful to make notes.\nSarah [Female]: Thanks for the tips, David. I will try it after lunch.\nDavid [Male]: Good luck! Let me know what you think.',NULL,'LISTENING','PUBLISHED','Listening Quiz',11,'','2026-04-20 15:18:28.699647',3,'2026-04-20 15:18:28.702157'),(49,'https://res.cloudinary.com/decqv3ed0/video/upload/v1776698014/file_lkp4fo.mp3','4.5','2026-04-20 15:17:12.941757',NULL,'They\'re talking about running marathon, answer all questions below:','https://res.cloudinary.com/decqv3ed0/image/upload/v1776698025/file_trvwjg.jpg','LISTENING','PUBLISHED','Running marathon',3,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2026-04-20 15:17:12.942757'),(50,NULL,'4.5','2026-04-20 17:23:33.156994',NULL,'Mark [Male]: Hi Anna. Did you finish the first quiz yesterday?\nAnna [Female]: Yes, I did. It was a bit difficult for me. I used my old notebook to help.\nMark [Male]: I think I did well. I studied with my brother on Monday. He is very good at English.\nAnna [Female]: That is nice. We have the second quiz today. It is about past events.\nMark [Male]: Oh, I remember. Our teacher said it starts at 2 PM in Room 305.\nAnna [Female]: I need to go now. I want to check my notes before it begins.\nMark [Male]: Good luck, Anna. See you there.',NULL,'LISTENING','PENDING_REVIEW','Quiz — Buổi 2',11,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2026-04-20 17:23:33.156994'),(51,'https://res.cloudinary.com/decqv3ed0/video/upload/v1776754714/ai_listening_1776754712168.mp3','3.0','2026-04-21 06:59:07.485525',NULL,'David [Male]: I am going to run a marathon. \nEmily [Female]: That is great. When is the marathon? \nDavid [Male]: It is next month. \nEmily [Female]: I ran a marathon last year. \nDavid [Male]: How was it? \nEmily [Female]: It was very hard. \nDavid [Male]: I am training every day. \nEmily [Female]: You will do well.',NULL,'LISTENING','PUBLISHED','marathon',11,'','2026-04-23 06:16:12.601581',3,'2026-04-23 06:16:12.602583'),(52,NULL,'4.0','2026-04-27 13:22:33.058268',NULL,'People are worried about the environment. They want to keep the air and water clean. Many years ago, people did not think about the environment. They cut down many trees and polluted the air and water. Now, people are trying to protect the environment. They are planting trees and using clean energy. The government is also helping to protect the environment. They are making laws to stop pollution. Some people are using bicycles instead of cars. This helps to keep the air clean. Others are using bags that can be used many times. This helps to reduce waste.',NULL,'READING','PUBLISHED','Environment',3,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2026-04-27 13:22:33.058268'),(53,NULL,'5.0','2026-04-27 13:22:52.614947',NULL,'The environment has been affected by human activities for centuries. Many species have been extinct because of pollution and deforestation. However, some countries have been working to protect the environment by creating national parks and wildlife reserves. These protected areas have been helping to preserve biodiversity and reduce the effects of climate change. In addition, many people have been reducing their carbon footprint by using public transport, recycling, and using renewable energy sources. The government has also been playing a crucial role in protecting the environment by implementing laws and regulations to control pollution and protect natural resources. As a result, the air and water quality have been improving in some areas, and the number of endangered species has been decreasing. Nevertheless, there is still much work to be done to protect the environment, and individuals, organizations, and governments must continue to work together to address environmental issues. The effects of climate change have been felt all over the world, and it is essential that we take action now to reduce our impact on the environment. By working together, we can make a difference and create a more sustainable future for generations to come.',NULL,'READING','PUBLISHED','Environment',3,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2026-04-27 13:22:52.614947'),(54,'https://res.cloudinary.com/decqv3ed0/video/upload/v1777296210/ai_listening_1777296207346.mp3','5.0','2026-04-27 13:23:56.467300',NULL,'Robert [Male]: Hello Sarah. Today, we\'re going to talk about technology. Sarah [Female]: Hi Robert. I\'ve been reading about how technology has changed our lives. Robert [Male]: Yes, it has. Many devices have been invented, which have made our lives easier. For example, smartphones, which have been used by people all over the world, have made communication easier. Sarah [Female]: That\'s true. People have been using smartphones for many years now. In fact, most people have been using them to access the internet, which has been available since the 1990s. Robert [Male]: Exactly. The internet, which was invented by Tim Berners-Lee, has been used by people to get information, communicate with others, and even shop online. Sarah [Female]: Yes, and it\'s also been used by companies to advertise their products. Many companies have been using social media platforms, such as Facebook and Twitter, to reach their customers. Robert [Male]: That\'s right. Social media platforms, which have been used by millions of people, have become an important part of our lives. We\'ve been using them to connect with our friends and family, and even to get news updates. Sarah [Female]: Absolutely. And with the help of technology, we\'ve also been able to make online payments, which have made transactions easier. Robert [Male]: Yes, and it\'s all because of the technology that has been developed over the years. Many experts have been working on new technologies, such as artificial intelligence and blockchain, which will change our lives even more in the future. Sarah [Female]: That\'s exciting. I\'m looking forward to seeing what the future holds. Robert [Male]: Me too. It\'s going to be interesting to see how technology will continue to shape our lives.',NULL,'LISTENING','PUBLISHED','Technology',3,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2026-04-27 13:23:56.467300');
